steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"69gp8","text":"Reverse Transcription","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":21}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ul9o","text":"The LunaScript® RT SuperMix Kit will be used to reverse transcribe HIV RNA for preparation to perform the Primer Pool PCR assay. NOTE: LunaScript® RT SuperMix will be kept in the PCR Clean room.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5oq99","text":"Place 96-well PCR plate on an Eppendorf® PCR cooler (stored at -20oC).   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ctn67","text":"Using a repeater pipettor aliquot 4 μl of LunaScript® RT SuperMix into each sample well of a 96‑well PCR plate according to plate map.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"559b1","text":"Cover the plate and move the PCR plate containing master mix from the PCR Clean Room to the processing bench for sample addition.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fasf5","text":"Add 16 μl of RNA extract to the appropriate sample well and gently mix by pipetting up and down. If less than 16 μl is available, make up the volume with nuclease-free water. Total volume = 20 μl per well.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4q6ok","text":"Seal the plate with MicroAmp™ 8-cap strips and briefly centrifuge to collect droplets.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5rmt5","text":"Return the RT plate to the Eppendorf® PCR cooler until thermocycler reaches 25oC.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"45il5","text":"10.  Load the plate into the SimpliAmp™ thermocycler, then run the “HIV REVERSE TRANSCRIPTION” method with the following parameters:  Set heated lid to 105oC  / Runtime ~14 minutes ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bfa6g","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6v97h","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1trac","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1d5pi","text":"     REPS      1      1      1      Hold        TIME      2:00      10:00      1:00      ∞        TEMP      25oC      55oC      95oC      4oC   ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":144}],"data":{}},{"key":"55vn6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f3m6n","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"302ar","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"tables","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"cellsMeta":{"0_0":"","0_1":"","0_2":"","0_3":"","0_4":"","1_0":"","1_1":"","1_2":"","1_3":"","1_4":"","2_0":"","2_1":"","2_2":"","2_3":"","2_4":""},"colTitles":[],"colWidths":[78,70,74,70,70],"data":[["  REPS  ","  1  ","  1  ","  1  ","  Hold  "],["  TIME  ","  2:00  ","  10:00  ","  1:00  ","  ∞  "],["  TEMP  ","  25oC  ","  55oC  ","  95oC  ","  4oC  "]],"guid":"85EAD65844A611EDB19C0A58A9FEAC02","isJexcelDataFormat":true,"legend":"","mergeCells":[],"printData":[["  REPS  ","  1  ","  1  ","  1  ","  Hold  "],["  TIME  ","  2:00  ","  10:00  ","  1:00  ","  ∞  "],["  TEMP  ","  25oC  ","  55oC  ","  95oC  ","  4oC  "]],"rowHeights":[]}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1neu6","text":"72.  Select the sample concentration as “ng/μl” with an input value of 1 μl.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"41r9u","text":"73.  Measure and record the library concentration.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ceru","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"blcer","text":"A total volume of 11 μl is required for the following step.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"et8la","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6qlpu","text":"If concentration of the total pool is less than 600ng/μl, use library pool undiluted.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cbjve","text":"76.  Add 1 μl of Rapid Adapter F (RAP F) to the 11 μl normalized barcoded DNA and mix gently.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"arb68","text":"77.  Incubate at room temperature for 5 minutes.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"72jda","text":"78.  After incubation, place the prepared library in a cold rack until ready to load onto the SpotON flowcell.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"po8f","text":"Priming and Loading the SpotON Flow Cell","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":40}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8rdg9","text":"Thaw the Sequencing Buffer II (SBII), Loading Beads II (LBII) or Loading Solution (LS, if using), Flush Tether (FLT) and Flush Buffer (FB) at room temperature.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bjbk8","text":"81.  Mix the SBII, FB and FLT tubes by vortexing. Spin down the SBII and FLT tubes.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a4t6v","text":"82.  Open the ONT sequencer lid and slide the flow cell under the clip. Press down firmly on the flow cell to ensure correct thermal and electrical contact.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2hktj","text":"83.  QC the SpotON flowcell using the MinKNOW software before proceeding. QC passes if total active pores are \u003e800.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"83ee2","text":"84.  After QC is complete, move the unit including the flowcell to the bench for priming and loading.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"638dg","text":"85.  Slide the priming port cover clockwise to open the priming port.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fuog0","text":"Prime and load the SpotON Flow Cell","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":35}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ftcu","text":" In a 1.5 ml Eppendorf LoBind tube, prepare the flow cell priming mix by adding 30 μl of Flush Tether (FLT) to 1.17 ml of Flush Buffer (FB) and vortex to mix.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"33fpu","text":"88.  Open the priming port and check for a small air bubble under the cover. Draw back a small volume to remove any bubbles (a few μl)   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"aae0u","text":"89.  Set a P1000 to 200 μl   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4f6to","text":"90.  Insert the tip into the priming port   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e43nh","text":"91.  Turn the wheel until the dial shows 220-230 μl, or until you can see a small volume of buffer entering the pipette tip.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2l1ji","text":"92.  Visually inspect that there is continuous buffer from the priming port across the sensor array.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"77u1b","text":"93.  Load 800 ul of the priming mix into the flow cell via the priming port without introducing bubbles. Wait 5 minutes.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9s4fg","text":"Prepare the library for loading","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":31}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cunp4","text":"Thoroughly mix the contents of the Loading Beads II (LBII) by pipetting up and down. The LBII tube contains a suspension of beads that settle very quickly. It is vital that they are mixed immediately before use.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8um0l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f6r80","text":"In a new tube, prepare the library for loading as follows:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1bnps","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2v5q","text":"Reagent                                                    Volume","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":7},{"style":"bold","offset":59,"length":6},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":7},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":59,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ck4dd","text":"Sequencing Buff II (SBII)                         37.5 μl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"44dk3","text":"Loading Beads II                                       22.5 μl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"64og1","text":"DNA Library                                               12 μl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":11},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":58,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cd3jl","text":"Total volume                                              75 μl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":12},{"style":"bold","offset":58,"length":5}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"24ov3","text":"Complete the flow cell priming","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7a8hq","text":"Gently lift the SpotON sample port cover to make the sample port accessible.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"79f5o","text":"Slowly load 200 ul of the priming mix into the flow cell via the priming port (not the SpotON sample port), avoiding the instruction of bubbles.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"28r39","text":"  Immediately, mix the prepared library by pipetting up and down gently.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6tk93","text":"Add 75 μl of sample to the flow cell via the SpotON port in a dropwise manner. Ensure each drop flows into the port before adding the next.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"227j6","text":"  Replace the SpotON sample port cover, making sure it is seated correctly, close the priming port, and close the sequencer lid.   Proceed to sequencing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
